===Etymology 1===
Possibly related to {{och-l|冰|tr=*p.rəŋ|ice}} ({{zh-ref|Baxter & Sagart, 2014}}); if so, also related to {{och-l|凌|tr=*[r]əŋ ~ p.rəŋ|ice}} and from {{inh|zh|sit-pro|*r-p(w)am||to freeze; snow}} (provisionally reconstructed) (STEDT); other comparanda are {{och-l|雱|tr=*pʰˁaŋ}} "heavy snowfall", and {{och-l|霙|tr=*ʔraŋ}} "sleet, snowflake".

